definitions.definition: A Haeckelian division of morphology ; the science of organic individuality constituting the purely structural portion of morphology , in which the organism is regarded as composed of organic individuals of different orders , each organ being considered an individual.

main_definition: ( biology ) A Haeckelian division of morphology ; the science of organic individuality constituting the purely structural portion of morphology , in which the organism is regarded as composed of organic individuals of different orders , each organ being considered an individual.
